<font color="#FF0000">POETRY WRITING MADE EASIER</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 18 20:47:05 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
       ode to silent protestor:<br><br>
your poem, of which your father decried,<br>
is a spark of truth, in a site of lies,<br>
for this site is filled with jokers and vets,<br>
commies and creeps, even some are mom's pets,<br>
but the common thread, that runs quite true,<br>
is we all are patriots, for the red, white, &amp; blue,<br>
be you jungle warrior or protestor loud,<br>
your judge be history, and you both stand proud,<br>
years later we know the truth and the lies,<br>
incredible how knowledge grows as time flys,<br>
from rambo fanatics to little commies,<br>
most of you still need to run to your mommy,<br>
but anyone can &quot;right&quot; a poem, such as this,<br>
but among you guys, a post is as good as a kiss,<br>
when will you deal with reality's cold stare,<br>
and lay out your souls, so cold, empty, and bare?<br>
Those that were true, and brave, and bold,<br>
have long left this site, to brains on hold.<br><br>
To bad the best post by MTF is taken back because<br>
he was too chicken to own it, afraid that his &quot;foxhole<br>
buddies&quot; (i.e. bubba's) wouldn't like it.<br><br>

<p><code>-- anyone can write poems except viet vets  ( says another silent protestor) </code><p>


